title: Firefox fields visually replace - > with U+2192
content: Firefox just started, seemingly unprompted, replacing - > (without the space) with U+2192. Just visually, however, as moving the cursor left from the end of -> puts it between - and >. This only occurs in Firefox fields such as the url search bar, settings search, Ctrl+F search, and the fields in this form. All other forms unrelated to Firefox as a product or company seem to function as expected.
